1	/**
2	 * protected-routes-401.spec.ts
3	 *
4	 * Gap closed: the existing suite had no 401 coverage outside of voice-access.spec.ts.
5	 * Every other module's protected endpoints were untested for unauthenticated and
6	 * invalid-token scenarios.
7	 *
8	 * Scenario matrix (no DB fixtures required — auth guards fire before service logic):
9	 *
10	 *   A. No Authorization header             → 401  (all protected modules)
11	 *   B. Malformed / invalid JWT             → 401  (all protected modules)
12	 *   C. Well-formed JWT with wrong signature → 401  (all protected modules)
13	 *   D. Correct JWT but wrong role          → 403  (admin-only + role-restricted endpoints)
14	 *
15	 * The FAKE_UUID is a syntactically valid UUID that matches no real record.
16	 * Route params must be UUID-shaped for ParseUUIDPipe to pass; without a token the
17	 * UUID is never reached by the service, so no DB row is required.
18	 *
19	 * Risk closed:
20	 *   - Confirms JwtAuthGuard is wired on every module (not accidentally removed).
21	 *   - Confirms tampered-signature JWTs are rejected (not just malformed strings).
22	 *   - Confirms RolesGuard rejects callers with insufficient roles before any DB I/O.
23	 *   - Catches future accidental public annotation of currently-protected routes.
24	 */
